It is thought to have evolved from a computer virus that would infect the computers aboard ships and the like, then knock their direction and course out of order. It bundles up its innumerable, multiplying tentacles and takes on a humanoid appearance, but its natural shape is a strange evolution of a Mollusk Digimon. Its Special Move is throwing its trident, with tremendous physical strength ( Forbidden Trident ). For its defeated opponents, it holds the rosary around its neck, and adopts a pose similar to mourning. extracted.textSample: Digimon Adventure 02 - Wikimon - The #1 Digimon wiki Digimon Adventure 02 From Wikimon Director Yukio Kaizawa Kakudou Hiroyuki Screenwriter Maekawa Atsushi Yoshimura Genki Character Design Animator Character Designer Nakatsuru Katsuyoshi Animation Director Nobuzane Setsuko Producer Seki Hiromi Planning Assistant Composer Arisawa Takanori Studio Toei Animation Network Fuji TV Duration April 2, 2000 - March 25, 2001 August 19, 2000 - May 19, 2001 Official Site Digimon Adventure 02 Official Site Next Series Digimon Tamers Previous Series Digimon Adventure Episodes Digimon Adventure 02 (デジモンアドベンチャー 02 Dejimon Adobanchaa 02 ) is the second anime series of the Digimon franchise . It is part of the Digimon Adventure continuity . This season aired on Sundays at 9:00 AM UTC+9 on Fuji TV, replacing Digimon Adventure (デジモンアドベンチャー) commencing on April 2, 2000 and ending on March 25, 2001. The Digimon storyline was remodeled after its departing and was succeeded by the third Digimon series Digimon Tamers (デジモンテイマーズ) in the early spring of 2001, one year after Digimon 02's airing date. Similar to Yggdrasil, it wants a world where Digimon and Humans do not coexist. Has the form of Gennai who once helped the “Chosen Children” in the Digital World, but has no direct connection with Gennai himself. After Ordinemon was defeated, it disappeared into a “distortion”. Digimon Adventure [ edit ] Digimon Adventure 02 [ edit ] At some point between Digimon Adventure and Digimon Adventure 02, Ken was transported into this world. When he submerged his Digivice into the Dagomon's Ocean, it changed into a black D-3 and he began his change into the Digimon Kaiser. In Digimon Adventure 02 - Episode 13 , Hikari was transported there. She encountered what first appeared to be Hangyomon lacking diving gear, with Evil Spirals on their person. However, the Evil Spirals did not seem to be controlling them, but instead sapped their energy. They said the god they worshiped had done this to them.
